Those of you Imagine users with a CD-ROM might want to check out
a CD called Graphic Textures (InPrint Art Library) by a company called
Allegro New-Media. I picked it up at a local Computer Show. It has 101
textures ranging from Marble, wood planks, jelly beans to camouflage and
green grass....all in .TIF 24-bit format that Imagine imports
beautifully. It even has 256 color grayscales of the same pics for bump
mapping! As an added bonus, it comes with a color poster showing all
the images and filenames. Best $12 I ever spent!
