@node IML-32 " MSG-32  Subject: Re: Bright object with shadows?
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Bright object with shadows?
Date:    Sun, 16 Apr 1995 21:48:21 
From:    rbyrne@3dform.edex.edu.au (Robert Byrne) (Robert Byrne)

Hello Jim, in <Pine.BSI.3.91.950415210851.26442A-100000@en.com>
on Apr 15 you wrote:

> Does anyone have any idea how to make an object bright and yet still have
> shadows from other objects cast on it?  I have version 3.2 for the PC.
> Thanks in advance.

Bright objects don't have shading and are not affected by lights. This
simulates real life like LED's on a panel, they're not affected by shadows.

