Date:    Sat, 22 Apr 1995 00:11:00 
From:    m.rubin9@genie.geis.com

 
 
 
Well the final outcome is probably not good for those of us who care about the
Amiga's future: During the lunch recess ESCOM increased its bid to $10 Million
and the creditors bought it. Although the meaning of this is still not clear,
it would seem to mean that CEI, despite Alex Amor's confidence, is out of the
picture. And Escom's committment to the Amiga doesn't seem to be very strong,
although they have not made a definitive statement in this regard.
 
I believe that Dan Stets was going to try to get an interview with the ESCOM
people and I will give him a call later. If there's anything more to report I
will post. Sorry that my efforts as cub reporter have brought what is
probably gloomy news.
 
