              gfx/3d/TextureStudio.lha

      It renders Imagine3 textures on an 020+/co-pro computer. Rendering 
onto spheres/plane/cylinders. Shareware version is limited to 
manipulating only the first 8 (of 16) texture variables. (Basically 
'Forge' for imagine textures)

      It's neat. Get it. Play with it. And wonder why impulse didn't have 
one of their own ages ago.

