@node IML-229 " MSG-229  Subject: Imag 2.0 PC and mem
@toc contents

Subject: Imag 2.0 PC and mem
Date:    Fri, 28 Apr 1995 14:56:55 
From:    surentrr@vax.sbu.ac.uk

Hi to all, I just made a discovery while using imagine 2.0 :

If you want to render a anim or still
quickrender a object in the detail or stage editor and you
get an out of RAM message dont lose hope ! I've found that for some objects
which require a bit more mem than your own config, render fine in the project ed
itor. This is due to the fact that the wireframe/shaded viewports in imagine
require memory . But in the project editor this memory is not used.
So basically you set your scene up (lights/cam/objects) goto the project editor
and select new ,set the output options, click ok and render .

Ramesh Suren                                                                    
