Something that is true 24-bit not a 32 colour conversion.

I have used a 24-bit image of a pile of jewels (sapphire, diamonds, emeralds
etc) as a global brush for glass reflections - works well.

For chrome, my favourite is a pic (I think it came with OpalVision) with
large fluffy clouds. It adds a subtle tinge of grey/blue to the
reflections.

