@node IML-243 " MSG-243  Subject: Re: PC/Amiga graphics
@toc contents

Subject: Re: PC/Amiga graphics
Date:    Sat, 29 Apr 1995 05:15:39 
From:    Falko@aol.com

>  One thing you will NEVER see a PC do is allow you to format a floppy and 
>let you go off and do other things.

I've got better things to do than format floppies. If i need them I buy them
preformatted. Cost the same nowadays. And yes I admit the Amiga hardware does
allow this whereas the PC hardware has problems with this no matter what OS
is used, though you can in fact do this on a PC UNIX box.

>  The other thing a PC will never allow you to do is have pull-down 
>graphic screens.

Heads Up!! You ain't seen Win95 yet with full window drag. This could easily
be advanced to to screen dragging. Also PC's can have massive virtual
screens. We're talking on the order of 4096 by 4096 on some video cards.

>It is too bad that PC types just cannot seem to 
>understand the significance of true pre-emptive multi-tasking.

You mean like Windows NT, Windows 95, OS/2 Warp, Novell UnixWare, Solaris PC,
SCO Open Desktop, etc, etc. Admittedly some of these are fairly high up, but
even though, don't tell me about pre-emptive multitasking. Oh, by the way I
too am a die-hard Amiga Fan. But I can't afford to support a platform in
spite of practicality.

Falko

