@node IML-260 " MSG-260  Subject: Diminish intensity?
@toc contents

Subject: Diminish intensity?
Date:    Sat, 29 Apr 1995 23:52:56 
From:    Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org>

> From: amadaeus@ccwf.cc.utexas.edu
> 
> 
>    In imagine 2.0, how does one determine the rate at which the intensity
> of a light diminishes? 

Distance   Color
--------   -----
  100       255
  200       255    
  300       216
  400       162
  500       129
  600       108
  700        92
  800        81
  900        72
 1000        64

The light I used had intensities of 255, 255, 255. As you can see, 
illumination stays constant for 256 units, after which it drops 
exponentially by 50% every 256 units.



