On Sat, 29 Apr 1995, Andrew A Krieg wrote:
>                                       [...] I was wondering if there is a
> way to "mirror" an object so that I would have two objects, one being the
> relfection of the other.  [...]

Yep, although it is not well documented.  Just scale the object by -1 in
the direction you need.  It should work for grouped objects like your
hand too, but I can't be sure.  Let us know how Imagine handles it.

